Temporary Tables in SQL
..............
- it will exists till the session is opened

00
It is created like a normal table.
It is mainly used to store intermediate results.
It is automatically dropped when the session ends (behavior depends on the database).

Why Use Temporary Tables?

Real-Time Scenarios
Daily reports
ETL (Extract, Transform, Load)
Complex calculations
Data migration
Storing intermediate query results\

MySQL Example
Step 1: Create Temporary Table
CREATE TEMPORARY TABLE temp_employee (
    emp_id INT,
    emp_name VARCHAR(50),
    salary DECIMAL(10,2)
);
Step 2: Insert Data
INSERT INTO temp_employee
VALUES
(101,'Sunil',50000),
(102,'Anil',60000),
(103,'Ravi',70000);
Step 3: Display Data
SELECT * FROM temp_employee;

Output

emp_id	emp_name	salary
101	Sunil	50000
102	Anil	60000
103	Ravi	70000


Step 4: Update Data
UPDATE temp_employee
SET salary = 65000
WHERE emp_id = 102;

Step 5: Delete a Row
DELETE FROM temp_employee
WHERE emp_id = 103;

Step 6: Drop Temporary Table
DROP TEMPORARY TABLE temp_employee;

 CTE - Common table Expression
 ..........................................
 ...........................................

 CTE is a kind of temporary table which has the-- exisistance only for that q


Definition: A CTE improves the readability and maintainability of complex SQL queries by breaking them into smaller, reusable parts.
It is created using the WITH keyword.

Syntax
WITH cte_name AS
(
    SELECT column1, column2
    FROM table_name
)
SELECT *
FROM cte_name;

Real-Time Banking Example
.................................

Account Table

Account_Id	Customer_Name	Balance	Branch

101	Sunil	50000	Hyderabad
102	Ravi	70000	Chennai
103	John	30000	Hyderabad
104	David	90000	Mumbai

Example 1: Find Customers with Balance > 50,000

WITH HighBalanceAccounts AS
(
    SELECT *
    FROM Account
    WHERE Balance > 50000
)
SELECT *
FROM HighBalanceAccounts;

Output

Account_Id	Customer_Name	Balance
102	Ravi	70000
104	David	90000

Example 3: Multiple CTEs
WITH Deposits AS
(
    SELECT Customer_Name, Balance
    FROM Account
),
HighBalance AS
(
    SELECT *
    FROM Deposits
    WHERE Balance > 50000
)
SELECT *
FROM HighBalance;

Example 4: Join with CTE
..............................
Customer Table

Customer_Id   	Name
1	            Sunil
2	            Ravi
Account Table
Customer_Id	Balance
1	50000
2	70000
WITH AccountInfo AS
(
    SELECT Customer_Id,
           Balance
    FROM Account
)
SELECT c.Name,
       a.Balance
FROM Customer c
JOIN AccountInfo a
ON c.Customer_Id = a.Customer_Id;



