SQL Normalization (Normal Forms)

Normalization is the process of organizing data in a database to:

Reduce data redundancy (duplicate data)
Eliminate data inconsistency
Improve data integrity
Make the database easier to maintain
Why Normalization?
Without Normalization
Student_ID	Student_Name	Course	Faculty
101	Sunil	Java	Ramesh
101	Sunil	SQL	Suresh
101	Sunil	Spring Boot	Ramesh

Problems:

Student name is repeated.
Faculty name is repeated.
Wastes storage.
Difficult to update.


Types of Normal Forms
..............................
First Normal Form (1NF)
Second Normal Form (2NF)
Third Normal Form (3NF)
Boyce-Codd Normal Form (BCNF)
Fourth Normal Form (4NF)
Fifth Normal Form (5NF)

For interviews, 1NF, 2NF, and 3NF are the most important.


1. First Normal Form (1NF)
...........................
Rule
Each column contains atomic (single) values.
No multiple values in one column.
No repeating groups.

❌ Not in 1NF

emp_id	    emp_name	skills
101	          Sunil	      Java, SQL, Spring

The skills column contains multiple values.

✅ In 1NF

emp_id	emp_name	skill
101	      Sunil	    Java
101	      Sunil	    SQL
101	       Sunil	Spring

Each cell contains only one value.




2. Second Normal Form (2NF)
...................
Rule
Must already be in 1NF.
Remove partial dependency.
Every non-key column should depend on the entire primary key.
Example

Student_ID	Course_ID	Student_Name	   Course_Name

101	         C101	              Sunil  	  Java
101	         C102	               Sunil     	SQL

Primary Key = (Student_ID, Course_ID)

Problems:

Student_Name depends only on Student_ID.
Course_Name depends only on Course_ID.
Solution

Student Table

Student_ID	Student_Name
101	Sunil

Course Table

Course_ID	Course_Name
C101	Java
C102	SQL

Enrollment Table

Student_ID	Course_ID
101	C101
101	C102



3. Third Normal Form (3NF)
............
Rule
Must already be in 2NF.
Remove transitive dependency.
A non-key column should not depend on another non-key column.

❌ Not in 3NF
................
emp_id	emp_name	dept_id	dept_name
101	Sunil	1	IT
102	Anil	2	HR

Problem:

emp_id
   ↓
dept_id
   ↓
dept_name

dept_name depends on dept_id, not directly on emp_id.

